Module com.example.rubankfx
Package com.example.rubankfx

Class AccountDatabase

java.lang.Object
com.example.rubankfx.AccountDatabase
public class AccountDatabase extends Object
Represents a database to manage multiple accounts. Provides functionalities for opening, closing, depositing into, and withdrawing from accounts. Also supports sorting and printing account data.
Author:
Arun Felix, Digvijay Singh

    • getAccountByProfileAndType

      public Account getAccountByProfileAndType(Profile profile, String type)
      Retrieves an account from the database based on the provided profile and account type. It iterates through the stored accounts, and if an account with a matching profile and type is found, it is returned.
      Parameters:
      profile - The profile of the account holder.
      type - The type of account to retrieve (e.g., "Checking", "Savings", etc.).
      Returns:
      The Account object that matches the profile and type, or null if no match is found.

    • getInterestInfo

      public List<String> getInterestInfo()
      Gathers information about the monthly interest and fees for all accounts in the database. The method will return null if there are no accounts to process. Each entry in the list contains a string representation of an account followed by its monthly fee and monthly interest in a specific format.
      Returns:
      A list of strings where each string contains details of an account's monthly fee and interest. If there are no accounts, the method returns null. The list ends with a marker indicating the end of the list.

    • updateBalances

      public void updateBalances()
      Updates account balances by applying interests and fees.
